external_knowledge:
- Least accurate models in this context refer to the top 5 models with the highest mean squared error (test_mse).;
- The identities of the models include their unique identifiers (model_id) and the measure of inaccuracy (test_mse).;
- Contact details of their makers include the users' full names (user_name) and email addresses (email).;

sql:
SELECT AVG(test_mse) AS average_test_mse
FROM models
WHERE created_by = 1;

SELECT DISTINCT users.user_id, users.user_name
FROM users
JOIN models ON users.user_id = models.created_by;

external_knowledge:
- Exceptionally low training error rates refer to models with a training MSE less than 0.005. ;
- Accuracy metrics in this context are inversely related to MSE values, meaning lower MSE indicates higher accuracy. ;
- The architecture description gives a brief overview of the model's design structure. ;
- The feature used refers to the specific node feature that was utilized during the model training phase.

sql:
SELECT models.model_id, models.architecture_id
FROM models
INNER JOIN architectures ON models.architecture_id = architectures.architecture_id;

SELECT model_id, architecture_id, train_mse
FROM models
WHERE train_mse = (SELECT MAX(train_mse) FROM models);

